  "text": "Fluorescence Acrylamide quenching studies of HYPK in the presence of Ca 2+ or GdmCl were performed by adding aliquots from a stock solution of acrylamide into a cuvette containing 70 μM of protein, previously incubated with either 0, 0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9, 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5 M CaCl 2 or 0.5, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6 M GdmCl for 2 h. Fluorescence quenching data were analyzed using the Stern-Volmer equation for dynamic quenching [CITATION_1] :",
